From: David Bauer <mail@david-bauer.net>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 23:29:39 +0100
Subject: wifi: mac80211: subtract power save airtime from AQL total

This subtracts the airtime of power saving STAs from the total pending
airtime when deciding of the eligibility to transmit a given TXQ.

This is necessary in case the driver buffers frames of power saving STAs
in hardware. A STA with a large amount of airtime retaining power save
mode can block TX for other connected STAs.

Subtracting the PS airtime from the total allows mac80211 to queue up
frames for awake STAs even when the total airtime of PS STAs would
prevent this due to AQL.

Once a STA wakes up, the power save total gets recalculated, removing
the now awake STAs pending airtime from the PS pool.

Signed-off-by: David Bauer <mail@david-bauer.net>

diff --git a/package/kernel/mac80211/patches/subsys/950-003-wifi-mac80211-subtract-power-save-airtime-from-AQL-t.patch b/package/kernel/mac80211/patches/subsys/950-003-wifi-mac80211-subtract-power-save-airtime-from-AQL-t.patch
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..8a06a6154202fce6098174d5d9a5c1e03aa2a24e
--- /dev/null
+++ b/package/kernel/mac80211/patches/subsys/950-003-wifi-mac80211-subtract-power-save-airtime-from-AQL-t.patch
@@ -0,0 +1,57 @@
+From fe6a5cf64b82f5a6cc37cc9ca05ab7d8d1baa53b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: David Bauer <mail@david-bauer.net>
+Date: Sat, 7 Feb 2026 09:34:31 +0100
+Subject: [PATCH 3/3] wifi: mac80211: subtract power save airtime from AQL
+ total
+
+This subtracts the airtime of power saving STAs from the total pending
+airtime when deciding of the eligibility to transmit a given TXQ.
+
+This is necessary in case the driver buffers frames of power saving STAs
+in hardware. A STA with a large amount of airtime retaining power save
+mode can block TX for other connected STAs.
+
+Subtracting the PS airtime from the total allows mac80211 to queue up
+frames for awake STAs even when the total airtime of PS STAs would
+prevent this due to AQL.
+
+Once a STA wakes up, the power save total gets recalculated, removing
+the now awake STAs pending airtime from the PS pool.
+
+Signed-off-by: David Bauer <mail@david-bauer.net>
+---
+ net/mac80211/tx.c | 16 +++++++++++++++-
+ 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
+
+--- a/net/mac80211/tx.c
++++ b/net/mac80211/tx.c
+@@ -4186,6 +4186,8 @@ ieee80211_txq_schedule_airtime_check(str
+ {
+ 	unsigned int num_txq = 0;
+ 	struct txq_info *txq;
++	int total_pending;
++	int ps_pending;
+ 	u32 aql_limit;
+ 
+ 	if (!wiphy_ext_feature_isset(local->hw.wiphy, NL80211_EXT_FEATURE_AQL))
+@@ -4197,7 +4199,19 @@ ieee80211_txq_schedule_airtime_check(str
+ 	aql_limit = (num_txq - 1) * local->aql_txq_limit_low[ac] / 2 +
+ 		    local->aql_txq_limit_high[ac];
+ 
+-	return atomic_read(&local->aql_ac_pending_airtime[ac]) < aql_limit;
++	total_pending = atomic_read(&local->aql_ac_pending_airtime[ac]);
++	ps_pending = atomic_read(&local->aql_ac_pending_airtime_ps[ac]);
++
++	/* PS frames can exceed the total in case driver delivers
++	 * TX complete messages prior to the STAs PS change.
++	 *
++	 * Handle this case here by accounting PS pending packets as
++	 * non-PS packets.
++	 */
++	if (ps_pending > total_pending)
++		ps_pending = 0;
++
++	return total_pending - ps_pending < aql_limit;
+ }
+ 
+ bool ieee80211_txq_may_transmit(struct ieee80211_hw *hw,
